        </ul>

        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">2. Circular averaging & smoothing</h4>
        <p>
          Magnetometer inputs commonly suffer from sensor noise. Rather than applying standard linear smoothing (which breaks when transitioning between 359° and 0°), this tool uses a trigonometric circular filter: averaging the sines and cosines of heading angles to deliver smooth, glitch-free needle rotations.
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">3. True North & Declination offsets</h4>
        <p>
          Magnetic North differs from True Geographic North depending on your location. Enable <em>True North</em> mode and supply your local magnetic declination angle to correct the reading.
        </p>

